						<summary>

						<p>On the north base of the Karivaradarāja-perumāḷ temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Kōṉēriṉmaikoṇḍāṉ (Vīrachōla ?): Year 1[9] = 1201-02 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>This damaged inscription records the order of the king addressed to a temple servant (name lost) granting a piece of land, together with <hi rend="italic">iṟai, puravu siddhāyam, elavai, ugavai,</hi> etc., situated on the eastern side of the big channel at ••• ••• śōḻaṉmādēvinallūr to the servant who performed worship in a temple (name lost) for the merit of the king on the Ēkādaśī day in the bright half of Mārgaḻi coinciding with the natal star of the king.</p>						

						</summary>
